Thousands of devotees made their way to temples and places of worship, on Friday, 21 February, in celebration of Maha Shivaratri.The religious Hindu festival is commemorated annually in honour of Lord Shiva â€“ who is considered to be the most divine among all Hindu Gods and the father of the whole universe. Maha Shivaratri is solemn and marks a remembrance of overcoming darkness and ignorance.  This major festival is observed by devotees who keep awake throughout the night chanting prayers, fasting and meditating on ethics and virtues such as honesty, non-injury to others, charity, forgiveness and the discovery of Lord Shiva.